1
00:00:36,800 --> 00:00:38,033
<i>Is it really so wrong
to swallow my pride?</i>

2
00:00:38,167 --> 00:00:39,033
<i> She's our mother, after all.</i>

3
00:00:39,167 --> 00:00:40,300
<i> So, what's next?</i>

4
00:00:40,433 --> 00:00:41,600
<i> Are you moving back home, too?</i>

5
00:00:41,733 --> 00:00:42,667
<i> No.</i>

6
00:00:42,800 --> 00:00:45,000
<i> FMP has no violations!</i>

7
00:00:46,300 --> 00:00:47,333
<i> Nice!</i>

8
00:00:47,467 --> 00:00:50,433
<i>What about the alleged
food poisoning incident</i>

9
00:00:50,567 --> 00:00:52,367
<i> at Luntian Park?</i>

10
00:00:52,500 --> 00:00:54,167
<i> It was an isolated case.</i>

11
00:00:54,300 --> 00:00:55,700
<i>Yes, to all our FMP family
and supporters...</i>

12
00:00:55,833 --> 00:00:59,567
<i>We've proven that the
factory's facility</i>

13
00:00:59,700 --> 00:01:01,333
<i> is clean and safe.</i>

14
00:01:01,467 --> 00:01:03,133
<i> They're back in business.</i>

15
00:01:03,267 --> 00:01:05,667
<i>But I'm sure they lost a fortune
during the closure.</i>

16
00:01:05,800 --> 00:01:07,200
<i> Let's have fun, okay?</i>

17
00:01:07,367 --> 00:01:08,633
<i> Mommy Pretty!</i>

18
00:01:08,767 --> 00:01:09,733
<i> Tetay!</i>

19
00:01:09,867 --> 00:01:10,867
<i> Tetay!</i>

20
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:12,333
<i> I missed you.</i>

21
00:01:12,467 --> 00:01:13,500
<i> I missed you, too.</i>

22
00:01:13,633 --> 00:01:15,533
<i> Jeff, try this afritada.</i>

23
00:01:15,667 --> 00:01:18,267
<i>I removed the fat and
added lots of potatoes.</i>

24
00:01:18,400 --> 00:01:19,700
<i> Isn't that how you like it?</i>

25
00:01:19,833 --> 00:01:20,867
<i> Jeff.</i>

26
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:21,600
<i> Son.</i>

27
00:01:21,733 --> 00:01:23,000
<i> Let go of me!</i>

28
00:01:23,133 --> 00:01:26,467
<i> Please be patient with dad.</i>

29
00:01:26,600 --> 00:01:28,733
<i> He's still hurting.</i>

30
00:01:28,867 --> 00:01:32,267
<i>But please, don't be
angry at him, okay?</i>

31
00:01:40,600 --> 00:01:44,967
Jeff, I know you're angry
at dad,

32
00:01:45,100 --> 00:01:46,333
but let's just stay calm.

33
00:01:46,467 --> 00:01:48,433
How can I stay calm?

34
00:01:48,567 --> 00:01:51,233
He's like a fly that just
keeps following me around!

35
00:01:51,367 --> 00:01:52,333
You know what? I shouldn't have
come here at all.

36
00:01:52,467 --> 00:01:55,633
I didn't want to see him
or his kid!

37
00:01:55,767 --> 00:01:58,100
I understand how you feel, Jeff.

38
00:01:58,233 --> 00:02:00,867
I'm also starting to feel
uncomfortable around Jessica.

39
00:02:01,000 --> 00:02:03,867
She sides with her mom
way too much.

40
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:06,767
If that's the case, then she
should just go back to her!

41
00:02:06,900 --> 00:02:08,233
Take her dad with her, too!

42
00:02:10,667 --> 00:02:14,967
I understand your anger,
your pain.

43
00:02:15,133 --> 00:02:16,667
But please...

44
00:02:16,800 --> 00:02:18,433
don't be disrespectful to Dad.

45
00:02:18,567 --> 00:02:20,067
That's enough, please.

46
00:02:20,200 --> 00:02:22,767
You're hurting him
too much already!

47
00:02:22,900 --> 00:02:24,067
Coleen, stop me.

48
00:02:24,200 --> 00:02:25,100
I might lose it.

49
00:02:28,367 --> 00:02:30,167
Why are you being so stubborn?

50
00:02:30,300 --> 00:02:31,967
This doesn't even concern you!

51
00:02:32,100 --> 00:02:34,033
Why not?

52
00:02:34,167 --> 00:02:36,167
It's my dad that your brother
is attacking!

53
00:02:37,900 --> 00:02:40,400
What is it that you don't get?

54
00:02:40,533 --> 00:02:43,267
This is our family's issue.

55
00:02:43,400 --> 00:02:44,800
Ours!

56
00:02:44,933 --> 00:02:46,100
That's enough. Let it go.

57
00:02:46,233 --> 00:02:47,967
No, Jeff.

58
00:02:48,133 --> 00:02:50,000
She's way out of line already.

59
00:02:50,133 --> 00:02:53,033
You're getting way too involved!

60
00:02:53,167 --> 00:02:56,800
You're not even part
of our family!

61
00:02:56,933 --> 00:02:58,533
Oh, yeah.

62
00:02:58,667 --> 00:03:01,933
And honestly? I'm glad I'm not
part of your family.

63
00:03:02,067 --> 00:03:03,867
Because I'd never want siblings

64
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:06,400
who are rude and don't know
how to forgive.

65
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:10,467
Coleen! Stop!

66
00:03:10,600 --> 00:03:11,667
That's enough!

67
00:03:11,800 --> 00:03:14,533
My brother and sister
aren't rude!

68
00:03:14,667 --> 00:03:18,767
If anyone here is rude and mean,
it's your mom!

69
00:03:18,900 --> 00:03:20,867
And look at you, you're starting
to take after her.

70
00:03:21,033 --> 00:03:22,433
You're showing your true colors.

71
00:03:22,567 --> 00:03:24,233
You're becoming just as nasty!

72
00:03:24,367 --> 00:03:25,967
You're nastier!

73
00:03:26,100 --> 00:03:27,500
- Let go of me, Jeff!
- That's enough!

74
00:03:27,633 --> 00:03:29,000
You're the one who's
just living off of us!

75
00:03:29,133 --> 00:03:30,167
Stop it!

76
00:03:30,300 --> 00:03:31,067
Coleen!

77
00:03:31,200 --> 00:03:32,833
Enough!

78
00:03:32,967 --> 00:03:33,900
- You're nastier!
- Coleen!

79
00:03:34,033 --> 00:03:34,933
Jessica, that's enough!

80
00:03:35,067 --> 00:03:36,233
Stop!

81
00:03:36,367 --> 00:03:37,133
- Coleen!
- That's enough!

82
00:03:37,267 --> 00:03:38,167
That's enough!

83
00:03:40,267 --> 00:03:42,233
Stop it!

84
00:03:42,367 --> 00:03:44,533
Have you no shame?
We have guests!

85
00:03:52,333 --> 00:03:53,833
<i> Tetay and I are leaving now.</i>

86
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:55,500
<i>Are you really not
coming with us?</i>

87
00:03:55,633 --> 00:03:56,467
<i> Come on.</i>

88
00:03:56,600 --> 00:03:58,733
<i>Mom even cooked afritada
just for you.</i>

89
00:04:18,533 --> 00:04:19,267
Wait a minute.

90
00:04:25,167 --> 00:04:27,500
Hey.

91
00:04:27,667 --> 00:04:28,567
Would you mind if I hang out
here for a bit?

92
00:04:28,700 --> 00:04:29,500
I thought you said you
were busy with work?

93
00:04:31,700 --> 00:04:35,600
Would you like coffee,
tea, water, or juice?

94
00:04:35,733 --> 00:04:36,700
No, I'm good.

95
00:04:40,133 --> 00:04:41,833
So that was just an excuse,
wasn't it?

96
00:04:41,967 --> 00:04:44,300
You skipped the
thanksgiving party on purpose.

97
00:04:47,933 --> 00:04:51,400
Do you know anywhere
I can buy afritada?

98
00:04:51,533 --> 00:04:53,233
Not the restaurant style.

99
00:04:53,367 --> 00:04:54,667
I want something homemade.

100
00:04:54,800 --> 00:04:56,700
Can we order?

101
00:04:56,833 --> 00:04:58,933
Are you craving it?

102
00:04:59,067 --> 00:05:02,633
You should've just gone
with your sibling.

103
00:05:02,800 --> 00:05:04,700
I'm sure your mom
cooked something.

104
00:05:10,233 --> 00:05:11,667
Go ahead, take it all.

105
00:05:11,800 --> 00:05:12,967
Yeah, yeah, sure.

106
00:05:13,100 --> 00:05:14,367
Share it, pass it around.

107
00:05:14,500 --> 00:05:16,067
Oh, wait, there's more. Here!
There's still palabok!

108
00:05:16,200 --> 00:05:17,700
Let me give you some, too.

109
00:05:17,833 --> 00:05:20,633
Here you go.

110
00:05:20,767 --> 00:05:21,667
- And here's some more!
- Grab a plate and pass it down.

111
00:05:21,800 --> 00:05:23,000
Don't forget the rice.

112
00:05:23,133 --> 00:05:24,500
It's not all about
the main dishes, you know.

113
00:05:24,633 --> 00:05:26,033
- Don't be like that.
- Sorry, guys.

114
00:05:26,167 --> 00:05:28,767
You all know why
we finished early.

115
00:05:28,900 --> 00:05:30,167
Go on, go on. Clean it all up.

116
00:05:33,300 --> 00:05:34,033
Here.

117
00:05:34,200 --> 00:05:36,133
Tala Diwa Restaurant.

118
00:05:36,267 --> 00:05:37,333
It's one of their
best-sellers.

119
00:05:37,467 --> 00:05:38,700
Chicken afritada.

120
00:05:38,833 --> 00:05:40,567
I've eaten there before.

121
00:05:40,700 --> 00:05:42,600
Tastes too commercial.

122
00:05:42,733 --> 00:05:43,900
I don't like it.

123
00:05:48,067 --> 00:05:50,233
You know how to cook, right?

124
00:05:50,367 --> 00:05:52,200
Can you cook afritada?

125
00:05:52,333 --> 00:05:53,633
I was actually going
to suggest that.

126
00:05:53,767 --> 00:05:55,400
Let me check what we've got.

127
00:06:02,133 --> 00:06:03,767
There are potatoes here.

128
00:06:03,900 --> 00:06:06,467
Okay!

129
00:06:06,600 --> 00:06:08,100
I'll fry them.

130
00:06:08,267 --> 00:06:10,233
I'm actually really good
at that.

131
00:06:11,433 --> 00:06:12,633
Carrots...

132
00:06:17,033 --> 00:06:18,633
garlic, onion...

133
00:06:18,767 --> 00:06:21,500
How do we do this again?

134
00:06:21,633 --> 00:06:23,100
Tomato sauce.

135
00:06:23,233 --> 00:06:24,533
No, don't use tomato sauce.

136
00:06:24,667 --> 00:06:26,100
Use tomato paste.

137
00:06:26,233 --> 00:06:28,767
And don't add chicken cubes.

138
00:06:28,900 --> 00:06:30,600
Fish sauce and salt,
that's all you need.

139
00:06:30,733 --> 00:06:32,733
That's the right way to cook it.

140
00:06:32,867 --> 00:06:36,667
The right way,
or your mom's way?

141
00:06:39,133 --> 00:06:41,967
Andrea, just admit it.

142
00:06:42,133 --> 00:06:43,967
You miss her cooking.

143
00:06:44,100 --> 00:06:45,700
Go to the party.

144
00:06:45,833 --> 00:06:46,833
If you don't want to cook
for me, fine.

145
00:06:46,967 --> 00:06:48,700
I'm easy to talk to.

146
00:06:48,833 --> 00:06:49,833
I'm not forcing you!

147
00:06:49,967 --> 00:06:52,000
- So don't, then!
- Andrea!

148
00:06:52,133 --> 00:06:53,133
Andrea, wait!

149
00:06:59,433 --> 00:07:01,033
That came out wrong.

150
00:07:01,167 --> 00:07:02,233
Stupid!

151
00:07:06,867 --> 00:07:09,167
This was supposed
to be a happy night.

152
00:07:09,300 --> 00:07:14,800
It's our thanksgiving
celebration, but you ruined it.

153
00:07:14,967 --> 00:07:16,800
Of all days, do you really
have to make a scene today?

154
00:07:16,933 --> 00:07:19,100
Aren't you even embarrassed?

155
00:07:19,233 --> 00:07:21,300
But, Mom, it's just that...

156
00:07:21,433 --> 00:07:24,100
Let me finish, Coleen.

157
00:07:24,233 --> 00:07:28,167
I've never hidden our family
problems from our staff.

158
00:07:28,300 --> 00:07:30,533
Because they're
like family to us.

159
00:07:30,667 --> 00:07:34,600
But did you really have to do
that in front of everyone?

160
00:07:34,733 --> 00:07:37,200
You didn't just disrespect me,
you disrespected all of us.

161
00:07:37,333 --> 00:07:38,333
Mom, this wouldn't have
gotten out of hand

162
00:07:38,467 --> 00:07:39,800
if they hadn't butted in.

163
00:07:39,933 --> 00:07:42,500
Can you please stop
already, Jeff?

164
00:07:42,633 --> 00:07:45,300
I'm sorry, Aunt Felma.

165
00:07:45,433 --> 00:07:47,633
I didn't mean for things
to blow up like this.

166
00:07:47,800 --> 00:07:49,700
I just feel sorry for dad.

167
00:07:49,833 --> 00:07:52,500
Jessica, but you
were still wrong.

168
00:07:52,633 --> 00:07:53,500
You went after your brother.

169
00:07:53,633 --> 00:07:55,900
Of course, he felt
disrespected.

170
00:07:56,033 --> 00:07:58,800
Dad, he disrespected you too!

171
00:07:58,933 --> 00:07:59,933
And not just today.

172
00:08:00,067 --> 00:08:01,900
He does it all the time!

173
00:08:02,033 --> 00:08:03,567
Aren't you tired
of being bullied

174
00:08:03,700 --> 00:08:05,400
by your own children, Dad?

175
00:08:05,533 --> 00:08:07,500
Enough already. You're not even
part of this, remember?

176
00:08:07,633 --> 00:08:08,767
Yeah, right.

177
00:08:08,900 --> 00:08:10,633
The fight should've been over.

178
00:08:10,767 --> 00:08:12,000
I'd already calmed Jeff down.

179
00:08:12,133 --> 00:08:14,133
But then you stepped in.

180
00:08:14,267 --> 00:08:17,400
Don't expect me to stay quiet.

181
00:08:17,533 --> 00:08:21,267
Aren't you always angry
when mom hurts Aunt Felma?

182
00:08:21,433 --> 00:08:23,267
That's how I feel about dad.

183
00:08:23,400 --> 00:08:26,067
I'm not going to let you
treat him like that.

184
00:08:26,200 --> 00:08:27,367
That's enough!

185
00:08:27,500 --> 00:08:30,467
We'll never end this if you all
keep blaming each other!

186
00:08:39,833 --> 00:08:41,600
I'm sorry, Aunt Felma.

187
00:08:45,333 --> 00:08:46,600
I'm sorry, Mom.

188
00:08:46,733 --> 00:08:48,600
I'm sorry.

189
00:08:48,733 --> 00:08:51,300
Aren't you tired
of all this fighting?

190
00:08:53,567 --> 00:08:55,067
We're family, right?

191
00:08:56,133 --> 00:08:59,100
We shouldn't be fighting
with each other.

192
00:09:00,633 --> 00:09:03,533
It's really stressful.

193
00:09:03,667 --> 00:09:09,267
We should be talking calmly.

194
00:09:09,400 --> 00:09:12,700
Listening to each other.

195
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:22,867
The kid gets it
better than you do.

196
00:09:28,933 --> 00:09:29,700
Bye, Mommy Pretty.

197
00:09:29,833 --> 00:09:32,133
Thank you.

198
00:09:32,267 --> 00:09:35,167
Thank you so much for coming.

199
00:09:35,300 --> 00:09:37,800
The dish is for your mom, okay?

200
00:09:37,933 --> 00:09:39,533
Oh, it's already with me.

201
00:09:39,667 --> 00:09:41,600
I'll go with them anyway.

202
00:09:41,733 --> 00:09:44,367
Mom, sorry.

203
00:09:44,500 --> 00:09:47,933
I know the mess started
because of me.

204
00:09:48,067 --> 00:09:51,467
It's just that your ex
keeps bothering me.

205
00:09:51,600 --> 00:09:52,867
Son...

206
00:09:56,100 --> 00:09:58,333
It's okay.

207
00:09:58,467 --> 00:09:59,600
It's okay.

208
00:09:59,733 --> 00:10:02,400
But, son, how much longer
are you going to keep...

209
00:10:02,567 --> 00:10:03,733
Mom.

210
00:10:03,867 --> 00:10:05,233
We just made up.

211
00:10:08,433 --> 00:10:10,067
All right.

212
00:10:10,200 --> 00:10:12,867
I'm not telling you
to leave, but...

213
00:10:13,000 --> 00:10:15,100
it's getting late.

214
00:10:15,233 --> 00:10:17,267
Tetay won't get enough sleep.

215
00:10:18,667 --> 00:10:20,767
Jeff? What time will our ride
arrive?

216
00:10:22,333 --> 00:10:23,100
I forgot to book it.

217
00:10:23,233 --> 00:10:25,400
Oh, Jeff.

218
00:10:25,533 --> 00:10:27,033
It's okay, Son.

219
00:10:27,167 --> 00:10:28,767
- Sorry, sorry.
- It's okay, Son.

220
00:10:28,900 --> 00:10:30,267
Wait.

221
00:10:30,400 --> 00:10:31,667
Use your car.

222
00:10:31,800 --> 00:10:34,267
Use your car already.

223
00:10:34,400 --> 00:10:36,833
It's just sitting there.

224
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:39,233
No one's using it.

225
00:10:39,367 --> 00:10:40,800
Come on, Son.

226
00:10:40,933 --> 00:10:42,667
Use it for Tetay.

227
00:10:42,800 --> 00:10:44,833
So you can take her
to and from school.

228
00:10:45,967 --> 00:10:48,367
Thank you, Mommy Pretty.

229
00:10:48,500 --> 00:10:49,667
Go ahead, Son.

230
00:10:53,800 --> 00:10:55,000
Thank you, Mom.

231
00:10:57,167 --> 00:10:58,033
Auntie. Tetay, come on.

232
00:10:58,167 --> 00:10:59,200
Oh, wait. I'll just get the...

233
00:10:59,333 --> 00:11:00,400
Hold on! Wait a minute!

234
00:11:00,533 --> 00:11:02,733
Wait!

235
00:11:02,867 --> 00:11:03,833
Ma'am.

236
00:11:03,967 --> 00:11:06,933
The afritada for Andrea.

237
00:11:07,067 --> 00:11:09,233
Thank you.

238
00:11:09,400 --> 00:11:14,433
Son, can you bring
this to your sister?

239
00:11:14,567 --> 00:11:15,633
Sure.

240
00:11:15,767 --> 00:11:16,967
I will, Mom.

241
00:11:17,100 --> 00:11:18,067
I'll just get the car.

242
00:11:18,200 --> 00:11:19,633
- Okay, Dad.
- Stay there, Sweetie.

243
00:11:19,767 --> 00:11:20,967
Okay.

244
00:11:27,400 --> 00:11:28,500
And then?

245
00:11:28,633 --> 00:11:30,567
The party ended just like that.

246
00:11:30,700 --> 00:11:32,233
Then mom scolded all of us.

247
00:11:33,633 --> 00:11:34,200
Is that all?

248
00:11:36,267 --> 00:11:38,500
That's what you came all
the way here to tell me?

249
00:11:38,633 --> 00:11:39,300
No.

250
00:11:39,433 --> 00:11:40,000
Actually...

251
00:11:40,133 --> 00:11:41,533
I brought something. Here.

252
00:11:41,700 --> 00:11:43,100
Mom sent this for you.

253
00:11:43,233 --> 00:11:44,400
Afritada.

254
00:11:46,200 --> 00:11:48,633
That's from mom.

255
00:11:48,767 --> 00:11:49,733
No, thanks.

256
00:11:49,867 --> 00:11:50,833
I already ate.

257
00:11:50,967 --> 00:11:52,300
What did you eat this time?

258
00:11:52,433 --> 00:11:54,600
Canned food? Eggs again?

259
00:11:54,733 --> 00:11:55,833
It's always the same.

260
00:11:59,533 --> 00:12:00,467
You know what, I'm heading out.

261
00:12:00,600 --> 00:12:04,000
Tetay and Aunt Paz
are waiting downstairs.

262
00:12:04,133 --> 00:12:05,467
What?

263
00:12:07,600 --> 00:12:09,733
The hailed car waited for you?

264
00:12:09,867 --> 00:12:11,100
They actually agreed to that?

265
00:12:11,233 --> 00:12:12,700
They're not allowed
to do that, right?

266
00:12:17,167 --> 00:12:18,200
So that's why!

267
00:12:20,167 --> 00:12:22,133
She gave your car back.

268
00:12:22,267 --> 00:12:24,133
I'm leaving, if you're going to
scold me, do it some other time.

269
00:12:24,267 --> 00:12:26,067
Congrats!

270
00:12:26,200 --> 00:12:28,800
And you left this.

271
00:12:28,933 --> 00:12:30,167
It's yours.

272
00:12:30,300 --> 00:12:31,267
- Don't bother.
- Mom said it's for you!

273
00:12:31,400 --> 00:12:33,000
- I don't want it!
- So you have something to eat.

274
00:12:33,133 --> 00:12:34,000
- Give it to the guard.
- You're doing this again...

275
00:12:34,133 --> 00:12:35,133
Put it in your car.
Let it stink it up!

276
00:12:35,267 --> 00:12:36,267
- What are you doing, Andrea?
- Go!

277
00:12:36,400 --> 00:12:37,933
Mom wants you to have it!

278
00:12:38,067 --> 00:12:39,200
I don't want it!

279
00:12:55,067 --> 00:12:55,900
Sweetie.

280
00:12:56,033 --> 00:12:57,833
How can you still
defend Jeffrey, Dad?

281
00:12:57,967 --> 00:13:01,533
Even after he keeps hurting you
again and again?

282
00:13:01,667 --> 00:13:04,600
Dear, he's your older brother.

283
00:13:04,733 --> 00:13:06,000
Dad.

284
00:13:06,133 --> 00:13:08,900
They've never really accepted me
as part of the family.

285
00:13:09,033 --> 00:13:09,600
Not Jeffrey.

286
00:13:09,733 --> 00:13:10,400
Not Andrea.

287
00:13:10,533 --> 00:13:11,267
And now...

288
00:13:11,400 --> 00:13:13,300
not even Coleen.

289
00:13:13,433 --> 00:13:14,900
You should call
older sister, Andrea...

290
00:13:17,233 --> 00:13:18,300
and older sister, Coleen.

291
00:13:18,433 --> 00:13:21,633
Give your siblings some respect.

292
00:13:21,800 --> 00:13:23,533
Especially Coleen.

293
00:13:23,667 --> 00:13:26,867
She's sacrificed so much
for us, especially for you.

294
00:13:27,000 --> 00:13:28,933
But, Dad...

295
00:13:29,067 --> 00:13:30,133
she's changed, too.

296
00:13:30,267 --> 00:13:32,333
She was only okay at the start.

297
00:13:33,867 --> 00:13:37,100
I don't think they'll
ever accept me.

298
00:13:37,233 --> 00:13:41,067
The only one who's ever really
accepted me is Aunt Felma.

299
00:13:41,200 --> 00:13:42,500
That's enough. That's enough...

300
00:13:44,133 --> 00:13:45,000
Stop crying now.

301
00:13:45,133 --> 00:13:47,367
That's enough, okay?

302
00:13:47,500 --> 00:13:48,467
Dad...

303
00:13:48,600 --> 00:13:51,100
Dad, I don't want this anymore.

304
00:13:51,233 --> 00:13:53,233
This is why we left mom, right?

305
00:13:53,367 --> 00:13:55,800
Because she was hurting us.

306
00:13:55,967 --> 00:13:59,567
But, Dad, it feels
no different here.

307
00:13:59,700 --> 00:14:02,633
They're hurting us, too.

308
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:05,700
Dad...

309
00:14:05,833 --> 00:14:07,133
Dad, I don't want
to stay here anymore.

310
00:14:07,267 --> 00:14:08,800
Let's just leave.

311
00:14:08,933 --> 00:14:09,900
Please.

312
00:14:11,133 --> 00:14:13,100
Dad, please, let's leave.

313
00:14:29,233 --> 00:14:31,800
What's with the drama now,
Manuel?

314
00:14:46,367 --> 00:14:48,900
Manuel?

315
00:14:49,033 --> 00:14:50,400
<i> Manuel.</i>

316
00:14:50,533 --> 00:14:51,800
Why are you crying?

317
00:14:54,533 --> 00:14:57,633
Oh, here's the mistress.

318
00:15:00,033 --> 00:15:01,667
Go ahead.

319
00:15:01,833 --> 00:15:04,267
Flirt all you want.

320
00:15:04,400 --> 00:15:07,267
Why not kiss right here
so I've got proof?

321
00:15:09,367 --> 00:15:12,267
I'm starting to lose hope

322
00:15:12,400 --> 00:15:16,800
that our children will ever
forgive me.

323
00:15:16,933 --> 00:15:20,700
Manuel, just a little more
patience.

324
00:15:20,833 --> 00:15:23,033
Just a little more time.

325
00:15:23,167 --> 00:15:26,967
What is there left
to wait for, Felma?

326
00:15:27,100 --> 00:15:29,800
I've been here for so long,
and nothing's changed.

327
00:15:29,933 --> 00:15:31,833
The kids still
haven't forgiven me.

328
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:36,767
If anything,
it's only gotten worse.

329
00:15:36,933 --> 00:15:40,033
<i>Maybe Jessica and I
should just leave.</i>

330
00:15:40,167 --> 00:15:42,167
Yes, Manuel. Please.

331
00:15:42,300 --> 00:15:43,733
Leave that house.

332
00:15:45,933 --> 00:15:47,767
Come back to me.

333
00:15:47,900 --> 00:15:49,533
Manuel, no.

334
00:15:49,667 --> 00:15:50,333
Don't.

335
00:15:52,767 --> 00:15:53,833
<i> Stay here.</i>

336
00:15:55,767 --> 00:15:58,000
<i> For what?</i>

337
00:15:58,133 --> 00:16:02,067
<i>Nothing good will come
from us staying any longer.</i>

338
00:16:02,200 --> 00:16:04,200
We should've left
a long time ago.

339
00:16:07,133 --> 00:16:11,867
But if you leave,
and the children comes back

340
00:16:12,033 --> 00:16:14,067
and you're not here?

341
00:16:14,200 --> 00:16:18,567
It would look like
you gave up on them.

342
00:16:18,700 --> 00:16:21,400
That we gave up.

343
00:16:21,533 --> 00:16:24,667
If you're not living here
anymore,

344
00:16:24,800 --> 00:16:29,867
the hope of them forgiving you
will drift even further away.

345
00:16:30,000 --> 00:16:33,500
Felma's such a flirt.
It's never-ending.

346
00:16:33,633 --> 00:16:37,733
You even used your children
to tie Manuel down.

347
00:16:37,867 --> 00:16:39,400
<i>Do you really believe
they'll ever come home</i>

348
00:16:39,533 --> 00:16:42,133
<i> while I'm still here?</i>

349
00:16:42,300 --> 00:16:43,267
Yes.

350
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:48,933
I believe you'll all
forgive each other.

351
00:16:49,067 --> 00:16:50,000
Why?

352
00:16:50,133 --> 00:16:53,667
Don't you believe anymore?

353
00:16:57,600 --> 00:16:59,433
I still hope.

354
00:17:01,800 --> 00:17:03,500
But believe?

355
00:17:06,833 --> 00:17:08,000
I don't know anymore, Felma.

356
00:17:08,133 --> 00:17:09,700
I really don't know.

357
00:17:11,000 --> 00:17:12,900
I don't know why we
became like this.

358
00:17:13,033 --> 00:17:15,033
I don't know why we broke apart.

359
00:17:15,200 --> 00:17:18,133
I don't know why I let
our family fall apart.

360
00:17:19,567 --> 00:17:21,567
Why did I let our family
be like this?

361
00:17:24,400 --> 00:17:26,167
<i> It's all my fault.</i>

362
00:17:27,900 --> 00:17:29,333
Everything's my fault.

363
00:17:29,467 --> 00:17:31,033
What else?

364
00:17:32,467 --> 00:17:34,733
I don't know either, Manuel.

365
00:17:34,867 --> 00:17:38,100
I have so many questions
in my life.

366
00:17:39,133 --> 00:17:41,800
What if I'd never gone
to Saudi Arabia?

367
00:17:44,067 --> 00:17:45,333
<i> What would we be now?</i>

368
00:17:47,067 --> 00:17:49,333
<i> What if I'd never met Hazel?</i>

369
00:17:50,667 --> 00:17:52,467
What if I'd been there

370
00:17:52,600 --> 00:17:58,200
<i>to watch Jeffrey, Andrea,
and Coleen grow up?</i>

371
00:17:58,333 --> 00:18:04,167
<i>What if we'd stayed a family,
and Jessica had been with us?</i>

372
00:18:05,300 --> 00:18:06,300
Monsters.

373
00:18:06,433 --> 00:18:08,300
What if I just go there
and stab you all?

374
00:18:12,567 --> 00:18:13,900
Sorry, I'm just
watching something.

375
00:18:14,033 --> 00:18:15,133
Got carried away.

376
00:18:20,600 --> 00:18:23,900
<i> Manuel, get some rest now.</i>

377
00:18:24,067 --> 00:18:25,300
It's late.

378
00:18:26,633 --> 00:18:27,833
Felma, wait.

379
00:18:37,400 --> 00:18:39,533
What are you even waiting for?

380
00:18:39,667 --> 00:18:42,367
Go on, kiss each other.

381
00:18:42,500 --> 00:18:43,600
Come on. Do it.

382
00:18:57,433 --> 00:18:58,633
Wait.

383
00:18:58,767 --> 00:19:00,600
I left my cellphone upstairs.

384
00:19:02,733 --> 00:19:04,900
I need to talk to Paz.

385
00:19:27,300 --> 00:19:29,067
Sweetie, pray before
you sleep, okay?

386
00:19:41,233 --> 00:19:43,833
Are you going to sleep
without kissing me goodnight?

387
00:19:43,967 --> 00:19:45,300
Nothing.

388
00:19:45,433 --> 00:19:46,867
I just don't feel
like doing it, Dad.

389
00:19:50,733 --> 00:19:52,367
Dear, do we have a problem?

390
00:19:56,433 --> 00:19:57,333
What do you think?

391
00:19:59,033 --> 00:20:00,200
Why are you answering like that?

392
00:20:02,267 --> 00:20:04,733
How am I supposed
to answer then?

393
00:20:04,867 --> 00:20:06,700
What's really wrong?

394
00:20:06,833 --> 00:20:09,500
Tell me.

395
00:20:09,633 --> 00:20:11,533
Are you angry with me?

396
00:20:11,667 --> 00:20:13,733
Are you hurt?

397
00:20:13,867 --> 00:20:16,533
Yes. Because the way you talk
to me feels disrespectful.

398
00:20:16,667 --> 00:20:18,700
Now, Dad...

399
00:20:18,833 --> 00:20:22,300
you know exactly
how your dad felt

400
00:20:22,433 --> 00:20:24,333
when you treated him
the way you did earlier.

401
00:20:32,967 --> 00:20:35,100
I'm sorry, Dad.

402
00:20:35,267 --> 00:20:38,133
I'm not disrespecting you, Dad.

403
00:20:38,267 --> 00:20:43,400
I just want you to feel
what Daddy Handsome felt.

404
00:20:43,533 --> 00:20:50,800
Because I was also hurt
by the way you treated him.

405
00:20:50,933 --> 00:20:54,800
All right, Sweetie. I get what
you're trying to say.

406
00:20:54,933 --> 00:20:57,600
But, you know what I went
through with your grandfather,

407
00:20:57,733 --> 00:20:58,800
don't you?

408
00:20:58,933 --> 00:21:00,067
Yes, Dad.

409
00:21:00,200 --> 00:21:06,700
But how many "sorry" does it
take before you forgive him?

410
00:21:06,833 --> 00:21:09,933
Isn't one enough?

411
00:21:10,100 --> 00:21:12,467
Just like with me.

412
00:21:12,600 --> 00:21:16,533
Even though you left me
for nine years,

413
00:21:16,667 --> 00:21:20,100
just one "I'm sorry" from you
was enough for me.

414
00:21:22,833 --> 00:21:24,800
I'm sorry, Sweetie.

415
00:21:24,933 --> 00:21:27,433
Back then,
you were still so young

416
00:21:27,567 --> 00:21:30,333
when I left you and your mom.

417
00:21:30,467 --> 00:21:32,433
You didn't feel the real pain.

418
00:21:32,567 --> 00:21:35,733
What's the difference, Dad?

419
00:21:35,867 --> 00:21:39,700
Wasn't it a real pain I felt

420
00:21:39,833 --> 00:21:43,467
every time my classmates
made fun of me

421
00:21:43,633 --> 00:21:46,400
for not having a father?

422
00:21:46,533 --> 00:21:48,667
That was real, Dad. It hurt.

423
00:21:48,800 --> 00:21:53,833
I even used to ask Jesus,

424
00:21:53,967 --> 00:21:58,133
"Does my dad not love me?
Was that why he left me?"

425
00:22:02,700 --> 00:22:05,567
Do you feel my love now, Dear?

426
00:22:05,700 --> 00:22:07,500
Yes.

427
00:22:07,633 --> 00:22:09,567
And you love me too, right?

428
00:22:09,700 --> 00:22:11,767
Of course, I do.

429
00:22:11,900 --> 00:22:14,367
Then try to imagine this.

430
00:22:14,500 --> 00:22:17,300
What if tomorrow you woke up,
and I was gone?

431
00:22:17,467 --> 00:22:18,433
I left.

432
00:22:20,300 --> 00:22:22,000
Found another family.

433
00:22:25,567 --> 00:22:27,067
And I never came back.

434
00:22:28,667 --> 00:22:30,167
How would that make you feel?

435
00:22:35,367 --> 00:22:37,767
That's what your Aunt Andrea
and I felt.

436
00:22:40,467 --> 00:22:43,633
Because we knew what
Daddy Handsome's love felt like.

437
00:22:47,367 --> 00:22:50,433
And then one day, he just left.

438
00:22:50,600 --> 00:22:52,033
That's the pain we felt, Dear.

439
00:22:55,833 --> 00:22:58,833
We carried that pain
for 18 years.

440
00:22:58,967 --> 00:23:01,467
<i>Is it true? Does dad really have
another family?</i>

441
00:23:01,600 --> 00:23:02,900
<i> Yes, my dear.</i>

442
00:23:03,033 --> 00:23:05,300
<i>Your father has
another family now.</i>

443
00:23:05,433 --> 00:23:07,667
That's why I'm afraid...

444
00:23:11,700 --> 00:23:13,167
to forgive.

445
00:23:15,967 --> 00:23:19,267
You know what I mean?
To love him again.

446
00:23:19,400 --> 00:23:22,467
Because what if he
leaves us again?

447
00:23:22,633 --> 00:23:23,400
What if the pain comes back?

448
00:23:23,533 --> 00:23:25,400
<i>Don't promise anything anymore!</i>

449
00:23:25,533 --> 00:23:29,033
<i>From now on, don't even
call anymore!</i>

450
00:23:29,167 --> 00:23:30,300
<i> Jeff, stop it!</i>

451
00:23:30,433 --> 00:23:32,033
<i>You don't love us anymore,
do you?</i>

452
00:23:32,167 --> 00:23:33,033
<i>- Jeffrey!
- Hello!</i>

453
00:23:33,167 --> 00:23:35,400
<i>Stay with your new family then!</i>

454
00:23:35,533 --> 00:23:39,467
Why are you thinking
like that, Dad?

455
00:23:39,600 --> 00:23:40,600
I don't know, Sweetie.

456
00:23:43,633 --> 00:23:48,033
Maybe that's what being left
behind does to a person.

457
00:23:49,867 --> 00:23:54,500
I hope, someday,
that fear goes away, Dad.

458
00:23:54,633 --> 00:23:58,133
So you can forgive
Daddy Handsome.

459
00:23:59,267 --> 00:24:03,100
Because we're wasting time.

460
00:24:05,033 --> 00:24:09,800
We don't know how long
we'll still have him

461
00:24:09,933 --> 00:24:12,700
or how long we'll still have
each other.

462
00:24:12,833 --> 00:24:13,800
Right?

463
00:24:15,867 --> 00:24:17,333
That's enough.

464
00:24:17,467 --> 00:24:18,433
Come here.

465
00:24:21,033 --> 00:24:21,800
Sorry, Dad.

466
00:24:21,933 --> 00:24:22,967
It's okay.

467
00:24:23,100 --> 00:24:24,900
You don't have to apologize.

468
00:24:25,033 --> 00:24:26,100
Stop crying.

469
00:24:42,367 --> 00:24:42,833
Mom.

470
00:24:42,967 --> 00:24:43,767
Jessica.

471
00:24:43,900 --> 00:24:45,867
Mom, what's wrong?

472
00:24:46,000 --> 00:24:47,733
Why did you ask me to come here?

473
00:24:48,933 --> 00:24:50,533
I need a shoulder to cry on.

474
00:24:52,233 --> 00:24:53,400
Dear...

475
00:24:55,500 --> 00:24:58,000
Felma and your dad...

476
00:25:00,300 --> 00:25:01,800
are having an affair.

477
00:25:02,600 --> 00:25:04,300
That's ridiculous, Mom.

478
00:25:04,433 --> 00:25:05,767
That's not true.

479
00:25:13,700 --> 00:25:15,967
Then...

480
00:25:16,100 --> 00:25:17,600
how do you explain this?

481
00:25:35,533 --> 00:25:39,067
Did you plant a hidden camera
in Aunt Felma's house?

482
00:25:39,200 --> 00:25:40,333
Yes.

483
00:25:40,467 --> 00:25:41,933
I wanted to catch them.

484
00:25:42,067 --> 00:25:43,933
What you're doing is illegal.

485
00:25:44,067 --> 00:25:45,733
Yes, illegal, then let it be!

486
00:25:45,867 --> 00:25:49,933
What matters is that
I proved my suspicion.

487
00:25:52,067 --> 00:25:53,833
Why would you install
a hidden camera?

488
00:25:53,967 --> 00:25:55,400
Are you stalking us?

489
00:25:55,533 --> 00:25:56,567
Hidden camera?

490
00:25:56,700 --> 00:25:57,600
Yes, Mom.

491
00:25:57,733 --> 00:26:01,300
I caught Jessica putting
a camera in the plant.

492
00:26:01,433 --> 00:26:03,033
You met with your mother?

493
00:26:03,167 --> 00:26:06,867
She showed me a video
of you and Aunt Felma.

494
00:26:07,000 --> 00:26:08,167
Is mom right?

495
00:26:08,300 --> 00:26:09,933
Is Aunt Felma your mistress?

496
00:26:10,100 --> 00:26:11,233
What did you say?

497
00:26:11,367 --> 00:26:13,167
My mom isn't a mistress!

498
00:26:13,300 --> 00:26:14,433
- Coleen!
- Take back what you said!

499
00:26:14,567 --> 00:26:15,633
Coleen, stop!

500
00:26:15,767 --> 00:26:16,833
- Coleen!
- Take it back!

501
00:26:16,967 --> 00:26:17,933
Jessica!

502
00:26:18,067 --> 00:26:19,000
- Take it back!
- Coleen!

503
00:26:19,133 --> 00:26:20,067
Coleen, stop it!

504
00:26:20,200 --> 00:26:20,700
Jessica!

505
00:26:20,833 --> 00:26:22,133
Coleen!

506
00:26:22,267 --> 00:26:23,333
Where's the spy camera?

507
00:26:23,467 --> 00:26:24,067
Give it to me.

508
00:26:24,200 --> 00:26:25,133
Is this what you're looking for?

509
00:26:25,267 --> 00:26:28,200
I'll sue you for wiretapping,
data privacy,

510
00:26:28,333 --> 00:26:30,033
and photo and video voyeurism!

511
00:26:30,167 --> 00:26:31,667
Are we competing over
who files more cases?

512
00:26:31,800 --> 00:26:32,633
I'll only file a single case.

513
00:26:32,767 --> 00:26:33,900
Concubinage.

514
00:26:34,033 --> 00:26:35,400
I'll have the man you're
obsessed with

515
00:26:35,533 --> 00:26:36,567
thrown behind bars.

516
00:26:36,700 --> 00:26:39,500
And you? I'll make you famous
on social media.

517
00:26:39,633 --> 00:26:42,133
I'll turn you into the
nation's number-one mistress.
